               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-999" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-999" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-999" type="surname" value="SPARKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-999" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS SPARKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a stable-keeper, at Ealing. On the 4th of June, I was in Frederick-street, Regent's-park, about half-past two o'clock in the afternoon, and saw the two prisoners—they had just joined together when I met them, and were about 150 yards from the prosecutor's—Allen pulled a pair of boots out of his pocket, and showed them to Brooks—he then put them into his pocket again, and passed by me—I watched them till they turned into Albany-street—I went on the way I was going—I went to Mr. Buer's shop, and went with his lad after the prisoner—I saw these boots fall from Brooks's apron.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1000" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1000" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1000" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1000" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD EDWARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Mr. William Buer, a pawnbro<lb></lb>ker. Mr. Sparks came to our shop, while I was looking for this pair of boots, which I had missed from a board outside—I went after the prison<lb></lb>ers, and saw them in Albany-street—they turned down a court, and when they came out of the court, I laid hold of both of them—Brooks escaped, Mr. Buer was coming up the street, and took him—I did not see Brooks drop any thing, but I saw this pair picked up, which are what I missed.</p>
